Very thin ca. 2cm-thick interval with rounded, dark green nodules (glauconitic?), possibly coupled with burrows.

Initial observations suggested that this is a sedimentary rock based on the fine laminations.However, smear slide and XRF point to an iron-rich oxide: hematite, limonite. This will be grouped into Unit II (volcanic) and is likely an alteration product of those volcanics.
